Subject: RE: [VB] dashboard fabric (-at-) speaker & radio insert

Thanks...that sounds like a good idea sandwiching stuff together. It is kind
of funny, that my recollection of the fabric was that it was similar to
vintage speaker covers, like the beige/brown/gold stripe on this page:
http://www.vibroworld.com/parts/tech10.html

But when I actually took it out of my box of old parts box, and saw it. It
is a bit more like burlap.

I've actually also been thinking of what to put where the radio was. I have
the original radio, but have since converted my bus to 12V. The radio also
had to be rigged to turn on and off with an external switch. I was thinking
of making a small metal box the same size as a radio, but where I could
throw my cell phone while driving...with maybe a little charger cord coming
out the bottom of the box.

I'll let you all know if I ever get to the box idea.


